{
  "id": "indus_phase21a_repetition_segmentation",
  "name": "Indus Phase-21a — repetition-aware corpus segmentation",
  "description": "Phase-21 follow-up to Phase-20 finding 4 (40/61 of M77 signs are NUMERICAL with rep_rate >= 0.20). Collapses runs of identical consecutive signs (\"A B B B C\" → \"A B C\"), then re-measures the bigram-transition spectral gap on both the original and the de-numerified corpus side-by-side. If the gap rises into the natural-language regime (>= 0.40) after collapsing, the M77 anomaly is dominated by repetition-block tokens and the residual corpus is closer to a real language. Output: reports/phase21a_repetition_segmentation.json.",
